/**
 * Filters body-level `#` headings out of rendered HTML.
 *
 * Blume already emits the page title as `<h1>` from frontmatter. Authors may
 * still keep a leading `# Title` in MDX for readable source and agent-facing
 * `.md` / llms.txt mirrors — this component drops those body H1s so they do
 * not duplicate the chrome title. Only MDX content uses this map; the layout
 * title H1 is unaffected.
 *
 * Prefer `##` for in-page sections. Mid-page body `#` headings are also omitted.
 */
---
